    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Risley</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To prevent Texas fever, now prevailing in America, importation of live cattle or
                    fresh meat from that country is prohibited in Denmark. Does the disease exist? I
                    have protested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Risley.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
